<task id="025" project="email-communication-solution-r3">
  <metadata>
    <title>Reply mode — pre-fill from source + sprk_inreplyto stamping + thread carry</title>
    <phase>Wave 1 — Engine + Wrappers + Sub-Components</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>3</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>020, 003</dependencies>
    <blocks>028</blocks>
    <tags>react, frontend, communication</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Reply pre-fill + sprk_inreplyto + thread-id carry are the load-bearing client side of reply-thread closure (success criterion 9). Subject prefix dedup ("Re: Re: …" avoidance) + body wrapping + association carry all matter. FULL appropriate.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>F</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <fr-refs>FR-11</fr-refs>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Implement `reply` mode behavior in `EmailComposer/modes/replyMode.ts` (pure logic) + integration in the reducer + send path.

    Pre-fill behavior (FR-11) — derived from `sourceRecord`:
    - `to` = `[sourceRecord.from]` (reply goes back to original sender)
    - `cc` = `[]` (Cc blank by default in Reply — Reply-All is out-of-scope for v1)
    - `subject`:
      * If `sourceRecord.subject` starts with `/^Re:\s*/i` → keep as-is (don't double-prefix)
      * Else → `Re: ${sourceRecord.subject}`
    - `body` = wrap original body with a divider:
      ```
      <blockquote>
        <p>On {sentDate}, {sourceRecord.from.displayName} wrote:</p>
        {sourceRecord.body}
      </blockquote>
      ```
      (For HTML body; for plaintext body, prefix each line with `> `.)
    - `attachments` = `[]` (Reply does NOT carry attachments by default per FR-11)
    - `associations` = `[...sourceRecord.associations]` (carry forward to new record)

    Stamping on send (FR-11 + dep on Wave 0 task 003 Internet-Message-Id):
    - When `send()` posts a Reply, the new `sprk_communication` record's `sprk_inreplyto` lookup is set to `sourceRecord.communicationId` (canonical client-stamp via the `sendCommunication()` API)
    - `sprk_threadid` (if present on sourceRecord) carried over to the new record
    - `BFF SendCommunicationRequest` extended with optional `inReplyTo: string` + `threadId: string` fields if not already present; communicationApi.ts wrapper passes them through

    Depends on Wave 0 task 003 (server-side Internet-Message-Id capture) so the inbound reply matcher (`IncomingAssociationResolver` per ADR-024) can close the loop. THIS task only handles the client-side reply pre-fill + outbound stamping; the inbound matching is existing R2 work.

    Files:
    - `modes/replyMode.ts` (NEW)
    - Update reducer to handle `mode === 'reply'` initialState + transition from view
    - Update send-path in engine to include `inReplyTo` + `threadId` in the request body
    - Update `communicationApi.ts` `SendCommunicationRequest` type to include optional `inReplyTo?: string` and `threadId?: string` — verify with Wave 0 task 005 + 002 that the BFF DTO accepts these
  </prompt>

  <role>
    React + TypeScript developer with email-quoting + thread-tracking experience.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `reply` mode pre-fills correctly per FR-11. Subject prefix dedup works. Body quoting matches the bodyFormat. New record's `sprk_inreplyto` set to source's communicationId. ThreadId carried. `npm run build` + `npm run lint` clean.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per FR-11 + spec success criterion 9 (reply-thread closure): client-side reply mode + Wave 0 server `Internet-Message-Id` capture + existing R2 inbound matching close the round-trip.

      Subject dedup: prevents the embarrassing "Re: Re: Re: Re: ..." chain from users replying to replies. Industry standard is single "Re:" prefix preserved.

      `sprk_inreplyto` is a self-lookup on `sprk_communication` (Wave 0 task 004 verifies it exists). The client stamps it on send by including the source's communicationId in the request body; the BFF setter on the server populates the lookup.

      Wave 0 task 002 added `AttachmentDriveItemIds` to the DTO. For reply, we also need `inReplyTo` + `threadId` — confirm during this task whether they're already in the request DTO or need to be added.
    </background>
