  <steps>
    <step order="1">Author `modes/replyMode.ts`:
      - `deriveReplyState(sourceRecord: IComposerSourceRecord): Partial&lt;EmailComposerState&gt;` — pure function applying the FR-11 rules
      - `formatReplyBody(originalBody: string, bodyFormat: 'html' | 'plaintext', metadata: { sentDate; fromName }): string` — quoting logic
      - `dedupSubjectPrefix(subject: string, prefix: 'Re:' | 'Fwd:'): string` — checks `/^${prefix}\s*/i`</step>
    <step order="2">Update `EmailComposer.reducer.ts`:
      - `initialState` handles `mode === 'reply' &amp;&amp; sourceRecord` by applying `deriveReplyState`
      - `SET_MODE` from view → reply applies the same logic + preserves `sourceRecord` reference for stamp-on-send</step>
    <step order="3">Update `EmailComposer.tsx` send-path:
      - When state has `sourceRecord` AND `mode === 'reply'`, include `inReplyTo: sourceRecord.communicationId` + `threadId: sourceRecord.threadId` in the `sendCommunication()` call</step>
    <step order="4">Check `communicationApi.ts` (post-task-005) for `inReplyTo` + `threadId` fields in `SendCommunicationRequest` type:
      - If present (added in Wave 0 task 005): use them
      - If missing: add them as optional + update `sendCommunication()` to forward them in the request body; coordinate with task 002 reviewer about whether the BFF DTO already accepts them (it should from Wave 0 task 003)</step>
    <step order="5">Smoke test in dev: load a record, click Reply, verify subject `Re: ${original}` (or no double Re:), to = original.from, body wrapped, attachments empty, associations carried.</step>
    <step order="6">Run `npm run build` + `npm run lint` clean.</step>
    <step order="6.5">Step 9.5 quality gates — code-review + adr-check.</step>
    <step order="7">Update `TASK-INDEX.md`: 025 ✅.</step>
    <step order="8">Update `current-task.md` per task-execute protocol.</step>
  </steps>

