  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Reply pre-fill: `to = [sourceRecord.from]`, `cc = []`, `subject` = single "Re: " prefix (dedup'd), body wrapped, attachments empty, associations carried.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Subject dedup: `Re: Re: foo` input → output `Re: Re: foo` (preserves), but `subject = "foo"` input → output `Re: foo` (adds prefix).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">On send, request body contains `inReplyTo: sourceRecord.communicationId`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`threadId` carried from source if present.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Body quoting respects `bodyFormat` (HTML blockquote vs `> ` plaintext prefix).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`npm run build` + `npm run lint` clean.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    Reply-thread closure success criterion 9 verification happens at Wave 2 UI testing (round-trip: send reply → recipient replies back → inbound auto-associates). This task lays the outbound stamp half of the loop.

    Reply-All deferred — Owner can request as a follow-up if needed; not in current FR-11 scope.
  </notes>

